lectors%20are%20striking%20in%20Birmingham%20over%20the%20city%20government's%20move%20to%20eliminate%20a%20certain%20role%20within%20their%20ranks.%20The%20industrial%20action%20has%20been%20rumbling%20on%20since%20January%2C%20but%20increased%20to%20an%20all-out%20strike%20on%20March%2011.%20Only%20a%20faction%20of%20the%20city's%20garbage%20collectors%20are%20still%20working%20with%20fewer%20than%20half%20the%20usual%20number%20of%20garbage%20trucks%20currently%20operational.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnite%2C%20the%20union%20representing%20the%20workers%2C%20says%20some%20staff%20employed%20by%20the%20council%20stand%20to%20lose%208%2C000%20euros%20(%2410%2C400)%20per%20year%20under%20a%20planned%20restructuring%20of%20the%20refuse%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWayne%20Bishop%2C%20a%2059-year-old%20driver%20and%20union%20member%2C%20told%20AFP%20that%20he%20would%20lose%20his%20position%20under%20the%20shake-up%20and%20be%20around%20600%20euros%20per%20month%20worse-off.%20He%20said%20the%20job%20was%20gruelling%20work%20and%20deserved%20to%20be%20paid%20fairly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20afford%20that%20for%20our%20toil%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20go%20out%20all%20weathers%2C%20we%20was%20out%20in%20Covid%2C%20we%20just%20can't%20afford%20to%20lose%20that%20with%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20going%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBirmingham%20City%20Council%2C%20however%2C%20disputes%20the%20union's%20account%20of%20the%20restructure%20and%20insists%20it%20has%20%26quot%3Bmade%20a%20fair%20and%20reasonable%20offer%26quot%3B%20to%20workers.%20The%20council's%20website%20says%20that%20%26quot%3Bno%20worker%20need%20lose%20any%20money%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20staffing%20changes%20were%20crucial%20to%20%26quot%3Bbecome%20financially%20sustainable%26quot%3B%20and%20modernize%20the%20waste%20collection%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECity%20Councillor%20Mohammed%20Idrees%20said%20he%20was%20also%20worried%20about%20Birmingham's%20reputation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20is%20known%20for%20its%20industrial%20heritage%20and%20rich%20multicultural%20makeup%20--%20but%20he%20said%20the%20strike%20was%20%26quot%3Bcreating%20a%20very%20bad%20image%20throughout%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ERodent%20Problem%20And%20Health%20Risks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20piling%20waste%20on%20the%20streets%2C%20the%20city%20has%20been%20infested%20with%20rats.%20Locals%20complain%20that%20rodents%20are%20entering%20their%20homes%20and%20cars%2C%20chewing%20through%20their%20valuables%2C%20costing%20them%20thousands.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20afraid%20to%20open%20my%20front%20door%2C%20they're%20everywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mary%20Dore%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20the%20city's%20Balsall%20Heath%20area%2C%20told%20The%20Guardian.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20run%20out%20from%20under%20the%20cars%20when%20you%20get%20in%2C%20they're%20going%20in%20the%20engines.%20They%20chewed%20through%20the%20cables%20in%20my%20son's%20car%2C%20costing%20him%20god%20knows%20how%20much.%20There's%20one%20street%20I%20can't%20walk%20my%20dog%20because%20they%20come%20running%20out%20of%20the%20grass%20and%20the%20piles%20of%20rubbish.%20One%20time%20I%20screamed%2C'%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20rubbish%20everywhere%2C%20rats%20everywhere%20...%20(they're)%20bigger%20than%20cats%2C%26quot%3B%20Abid%2C%20another%20resident%2C%20told%20CNN.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResidents%20are%20also%20complaining%20that%20pest-infested%20piles%20have%20started%20affecting%20their%20health.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20scary%20--%20I'm%20worried%20for%20my%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Abel%20Mihai%2C%2023%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20the%20Saltley%20area%20of%20the%20city.%20Mihai%20told%20AFP%20that%20every%20time%20%C2%A0his%20three-year-old%20son%20goes%20out%2C%20%26quot%3Bhe%20vomits%20from%20the%20smell.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20piles%20of%20garbage%20have%20also%20emerged%20as%20a%20fire%20hazard.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20bin%20fire%20on%20the%20end%20of%20our%20street%20the%20other%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20Mihai%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quarrel%20also%20plays%20into%20wider%20problems%20in%20British%20society%20--%20from%20stretched%20local%20council%20funding%20to%20sweeping%20inequality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResidents%20in%20poorer%20areas%20of%20the%20city%20in%20England's%20Midlands%20region%20told%20AFP%20they%20felt%20neglected%2C%20and%20questioned%20whether%20the%20trouble%20would%20have%20spiralled%20in%20wealthier%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitical%20Stink%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20garbage%20problem%20has%20now%20begun%20to%20cause%20a%20political%20stink%20for%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Keir%20Starmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConfronted%20by%20the%20opposition%20in%20parliament%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20he%20admitted%20the%20situation%20in%20Birmingham%20was%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20unacceptable%26quot%3B%20--%20but%20insisted%20his%20government%20would%20provide%20extra%20support%20and%20stood%20by%20the%20council%2C%20which%20is%20run%20by%20Starmer's%20Labour%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResidents%20are%20tired%20of%20waiting%2C%20though%2C%20and%20some%20have%20taken%20matters%20into%20their%20own%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20special%20waste%20truck%20visit%20on%20the%20street%20in%20Saltley%20on%20Wednesday%20was%20arranged%20by%20members%20of%20a%20community%20centre%20who%20contacted%20a%20local%20councillor%20for%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrganiser%20Hubaish%20Mohammed%2C%2026%2C%20said%20the%20Hutton%20Hall%20group%20had%20helped%20hundreds%20of%20people%20lug%20their%20rubbish%20to%20the%20temporary%20collection%20site%2C%20where%20residents%20load%20their%20waste%20onto%20trucks%20staffed%20by%20non-striking%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStaff%20said%20they'd%20helped%20colle