as%20one%20of%20the%20smartest%20large%20language%20models%20(LLMs)%20yet%2C%20and%20the%20most%20powerful%20version%20they've%20developed.%20It's%20intended%20to%20help%20train%20and%20guide%20future%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20rollout%20also%20marks%20Meta's%20first%20use%20of%20a%20mixture-of-experts%20(MoE)%20framework.%20MoE%20divides%20the%20model%20into%20specialised%20components-each%20focused%20on%20areas%20like%20physics%2C%20poetry%2C%20biology%2C%20or%20programming.%20During%20any%20given%20task%2C%20only%20the%20most%20relevant%20expert%20modules%20are%20activated%2C%20boosting%20efficiency%20and%20reducing%20costs%20for%20training%20and%20inference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EModel%20Highlights%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELlama%204%20Scout%20is%20built%20with%2017%20billion%20parameters%20and%2016%20experts%2C%20offering%20a%2010-million-token%20context%20window.%20Designed%20to%20operate%20on%20a%20single%20GPU%2C%20it%20reflects%20a%20trend%20toward%20lightweight%2C%20high-performance%20models-similar%20to%20Google's%20recent%20Gemma%203%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELlama%204%20Maverick%2C%20also%20at%2017%20billion%20parameters%20but%20with%20128%20experts%2C%20is%20intended%20as%20a%20general-purpose%20model%20for%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20assistant-style%20use%20cases.%20Meta%20describes%20it%20as%20a%20reliable%20%26quot%3Bworkhorse%26quot%3B%20capable%20of%20handling%20chat%2C%20reasoning%2C%20and%20other%20digital%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noindex%2Cnofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fai.meta.com%2Fblog%2Fllama-4-multimodal-intelligence%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMeta%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3Eclaims%20Maverick%20outperforms%20OpenAI's%20GPT-4o%20and%20Google's%20Gemini%202.0%20Flash%20across%20several%20benchmarks%2C%20including%20code%20generation%2C%20reasoning%2C%20multilingual%20understanding%2C%20image%20analysis%2C%20and%20handling%20long%20contexts.%20It%20also%20rivals%20DeepSeek%20v3.1%2C%20a%20much%20larger%20model%2C%20in%20performance%20across%20coding%20and%20logic-based%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20DeepSeek%20claimed%20its%20models%20could%20match%20those%20from%20leading%20U.S.%20firms%2C%20prompting%20concerns%20over%20increasing%20global%20competition%20in%20AI.%20However%2C%20Meta%20and%20Google%20executives%20have%20downplayed%20its%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20Next%3A%20Behemoth%20and%20Beyond%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%20in%20development%2C%20the%20Llama%204%20Behemoth%20model%20is%20expected%20to%20feature%20288%20billion%20active%20parameters%2C%2016%20experts%2C%20and%20nearly%202%20trillion%20total%20parameters.%20Meta%20says%20it%20outperforms%20GPT-4.5%2C%20Claude%20Sonnet%203.7%2C%20and%20Gemini%202.0%20Pro%20in%20STEM-related%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20also%20teased%20Llama%204%20Reasoning%2C%20a%20model%20focused%20specifically%20on%20complex%20problem-solving%20and%20analytical%20tasks.%20More%20details%20are%20expected%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20just%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Llama%204%20lineup%2C%26quot%3B%20Meta%20wrote%20in%20a%20blog%20post.%20%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20the%20most%20advanced%20AI%20systems%20must%20be%20capable%20of%20taking%20generalized%20actions%2C%20engaging%20in%20natural%20conversations%2C%20and%20tackling%20problems%20they've%20never%20encountered%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EScaling%20Up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeta%20revealed%20that%20downloads%20of%20Llama%20models%20surpassed%20one%20billion%20just%20two%20weeks%20before%20Llama%204's%20launch-%20up%20from%20650%20million%20in%20December%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20January%2C%20Zuckerberg%20announced%20the%20company's%20AI%20infrastructure%20spending%20for%202025%20would%20range%20between%20%2460%20billion%20and%20%2465%20billion%2C%20covering%20investments%20in%20servers%2C%20dat